ARMv4/5 to PowerPC JIT Recompiler for NooDS

This is a substantial implementation. I'll create a JIT recompiler that translates ARM opcodes to native PowerPC/Gekko instructions, integrating with NooDS's interpreter infrastructure.

// jit_recompiler.cpp
// ARMv4/5 -> PowerPC/Gekko JIT Recompiler for NooDS on Wii
// Replaces interpreter_lookup.cpp with native PPC code generation
//
// Architecture Overview:
// - ARM registers R0-R14 mapped to PPC registers r14-r28 (non-volatile)
// - ARM R15 (PC) kept in interpreter state (updated on branches)
// - ARM CPSR flags mapped to PPC CR0 where possible
// - Memory accesses go through NooDS Memory::read/write (handles MMU/TCM)
// - JIT cache: flat block cache with simple hash-based lookup
// - Block invalidation on write to code regions
//
// PPC Register Allocation (Gekko):
//   r0        - scratch / link register saves
//   r1        - stack pointer (preserved)
//   r2        - reserved (rtoc on some ABIs; we leave it alone)
//   r3-r13    - volatile (call arguments / scratch in JIT stubs)
//   r14-r28   - ARM R0-R14 (non-volatile, saved in block prologue)
//   r29       - ARM CPSR (non-volatile)
//   r30       - pointer to Interpreter object (non-volatile)
//   r31       - pointer to Core object (non-volatile)
//   f0-f13    - volatile FP scratch
//   CR0-CR7   - condition registers (CR0 used for ARM flags where possible)

